The paper deals with concurrent updates to a directed graph data structure, which is a classic problem in distributed computing (cs.DC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the implementation of a concurrent adjacency list, which falls under programming languages (cs.PL) and databases (cs.DB). The paper presents two algorithms for maintaining acyclicity, which involves graph theory (cs.LG).
